24/03/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Lulzim Krasniqi, described by local media as "Albania's mafia chief" in Croatia, has been shot dead in Zagreb, police said Thursday (23 March). 
The gunman waited for Krasniqi at the entrance to his apartment building Wednesday night, according to police. 
He was the alleged "head of the Albanian mafia" in Croatia and was often linked in the local press to the smuggling of drugs, arms and cigarettes to Western Europe via the Balkans. 
(Vecernji List, Vijesti - 24/03/06; AFP, HINA, HRT - 23/03/06)
